    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I understand the Fitzgibbon buyer pool and what drives competition in this market. The suburb competes directly with Bracken Ridge, Taigum and Zillmere for first-home buyer and investor demand, and getting the positioning and timing right makes a meaningful difference to your final result.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The Fitzgibbon Chase estate runs through the heart of the suburb and delivers the kind of contemporary streetscapes that appeal to buyers who want newer housing with low maintenance demands. Gateway Motorway access at Bracken Ridge Road puts the airport and northern distributor within easy reach, which matters to the investor and professional family segment. Taigum Square provides day-to-day retail within a short drive, and the surrounding park network gives the estate a more spacious feel than density alone might suggest. Investors in this pocket track rental yields carefully and move quickly when the numbers align.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #b98229;">
