    <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column;">

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What drives property values in Fitzgibbon?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Property condition and presentation are the primary value drivers in Fitzgibbon. The suburb's contemporary estate housing is judged by buyers against competing listings in Bracken Ridge, Taigum and Zillmere simultaneously. Homes that present as move-in ready consistently achieve a premium over comparable properties that show deferred maintenance.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Fitzgibbon?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Well-presented and accurately priced Fitzgibbon homes typically sell within 20 to 35 days. The first-home buyer and investor pool active in this corridor is comparison-driven and moves quickly when a property is correctly positioned. Overpriced properties tend to sit, as buyers have clear alternatives across the northern suburbs at similar price points.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in Fitzgibbon?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Fitzgibbon offers a modern estate lifestyle with parks and green corridors throughout Fitzgibbon Chase, easy access to Taigum Square for retail and dining, and Gateway Motorway connections for commuters. The suburb is popular with young families and first-home buyers who appreciate newer low-maintenance homes at an accessible northern Brisbane price point.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          Is Fitzgibbon a good suburb to buy in right now?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Fitzgibbon attracts consistent demand from buyers seeking contemporary estate housing at a value point in the northern corridor. The combination of newer builds, good motorway access and proximity to Taigum Square makes it appealing to both owner-occupiers and investors. Rental demand in this pocket remains solid, which supports investor confidence in the suburb.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

